.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-CONNECT-AUTO" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-connect-auto \- schedule reconnection to disconnected peers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-connect-auto
.SH DESCRIPTION
Lists peers that are currently disconnected and have known network addresses,
scheduling them for reconnection.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"reconnect_scheduled":N, "peers":[{peer_id, addr, status}]}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-connect (1),
.BR lightning-peer-disconnect-all (1)
